A halin da ake ciki, kamfanin gudanarwa na Wiley, A-List Management, "cut all ties" da tauraron.
Tsohon manajan mai zane a yanzu, John Woolf, wanda Yahudawa ne, ya rubuta a Twitter cewa: "Bi da kalaman Wiley na antisemitic a yau mu a @A_ListMGMT sun yanke duk dangantaka da shi. Babu wani wuri a cikin al'umma don antisemitism."
A baya ya ce ba ya goyon baya ko kuma ya yi ta’aziyya ga abin da Wiley ya wallafa amma zai yi magana da shi a kansa kuma ya " taimaka wajen ilmantar da shi."
Duk da haka, a wani bidiyo a Instagram, Wiley ya bayyana cewa shi ne wanda ya yanke dangantaka da gudanarwarsa.
Sauran 'yan majalisa sun caccaki Twitter saboda ƙyale tweets su kasance a bayyane.
Dan majalisar Labour Jess Phillips ya ce a ranar Asabar:
"Ka ga dukan Wiley stuff. Me ya sa a duniya sun @Twitter bar up irin mugun antisemitism da ƙiyayya? Yana hits dukan m beats, Yahudawa samun abubuwa ba ka samu, su ne a iko, suna zaton su mafi alh<unk>ri... Wannan shi ne m stuff. Tabbas ya kamata ya sauko."
Fellow MP Neil Coyle ya kara da cewa: "His management appear able to act quicker than @Twitter emphasising, once again, cewa dokokin (ciki har da Online Harms Bill) ya kamata tabbatar da kafofin watsa labarun dandamali ba a amfani da su don yada ƙiyayya."
